(One common difficulty in Data Structures is using a structure without understanding its) Tj
T*
(behavior. This matters because many learners can repeat a definition but still fail to) Tj
T*
(use it correctly. A real textbook lesson should therefore point out not only the correct) Tj
T*
(method, but also the exact place where students often go wrong. Learning improves when) Tj
T*
(the student compares correct reasoning with incorrect reasoning.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. Independent Study Guidance) Tj
T*
(For independent study, the learner should revisit the explanation and then practise with) Tj
T*
(tasks that reflect structure identification and use cases. The most effective habit is) Tj
T*
(to read the worked example slowly, restate each step in simple words, and then attempt a) Tj
T*
(similar question alone. This turns Data Structures into something the student can) Tj
T*
(genuinely study and understand without depending completely on a teacher.) Tj
T*
() Tj
